### What problem does this feature solve?
I want to pass top slots to lower component, and I have to use render function instead of template in my component when I use ant-design-vue.

```html
<template>
  <t-table-plus :columns="columns" :data-source="data">
    <a slot="name" slot-scope="text">{{ text }}</a>
    <span slot="customTitle"><a-icon type="smile-o" /> Name</span>
  </t-table-plus>
</template>
```

### What does the proposed API look like?
```javascript
import { Table as ATable } from 'ant-design-vue';

export default {
  name: 'a-table-plus',
  render: function (createElement) {
    return createElement(ATable, {
      attrs: this.$attrs,
      on: this.$listeners,
      scopedSlots: this.$scopedSlots,
      slots: this.$slots, // how to pass slots?
    });
  },
};
```

